  "safety_low": "Breathe at a comfortable pace. If you feel dizzy or uncomfortable, stop the exercise and breathe normally.",
  "safety_holds_generic": "This technique includes breath holds. Mild tingling in the limbs is normal; dizziness or tunnel vision is a signal to stop and breathe freely. Never practise this technique in water, while driving, or in any situation that requires focused attention.",
  "safety_intense": "IMPORTANT: never perform this technique in water, while driving, while standing, or while operating machinery — loss of consciousness is possible.\n\nContraindications: pregnancy, epilepsy, cardiovascular disease, high blood pressure, panic disorders, recent surgery, glaucoma. If any of these apply to you, consult a doctor before practising.\n\nStart with 3–4 cycles and increase gradually.",

